        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 6:16PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Eleanor, or near Winfield, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winfield, Hurricane, Eleanor, Buffalo, Poca, Teays Valley, Bancroft,
and Fraziers Bottom.

This includes Interstate 64 in West Virginia between mile markers 33
and 44.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
